<h2><b>Breeze::OS Installer -- Drives / Partitioning / Formatting</b></h2>
<p>
To <b>install packages</b> on your computer, the following steps are taken:
<ul align="left">
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>hard-drive</b></font> a hard-drive must be selected.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>scheme</b></font> a partitioning scheme must be selected.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>crypto</b></font> an encryption scheme may be selected.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>partition</b></font> automatic or custom partitioning is used.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>format</b></font> the partitioned drive must be formatted.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>filesystems</b></font> the selected ones must be setup.
</ul>
<font color="#33FB01"><b>UEFI</b></font> stands for Unified Extensible Firmware Interface.<br><font color="#33FB01"><b>UEFI</b></font> <b>should only</b> be used, if you have a computer<br>preloaded with <b>Windows</b>, which is <b>newer</b> than 2010.<br><b>UEFI</b> booting is only available in the <b>64-bit</b> release of our distro.<br>
<font color="#33FB01"><b>GPT</b></font> stands for GUID Partitioning Table.<br><font color="#33FB01"><b>GPT</b></font> allows hard drives greater than 2TB to be partitioned.<br><font color="#33FB01"><b>GPT</b></font> works with computers <b>older</b> than 2010; but,<br>should be selected for computers <b>newer</b> than 2010.<br><b>Windows</b> computers <b>do not work well</b> with <b>GPT</b>.<br>Only choose <font color="#33FB01"><b>GPT</b></font> partitioning, if your <b>bios</b> supports it.<br>
<font color="#33FB01"><b>MBR</b></font> stands for Master Boot Record.<br><font color="#33FB01"><b>MBR</b></font> is the <b>default</b> choice for <b>Partitioning</b> in the <b>scheme</b> page.<br>If you want to run a <b>standalone</b> system; and, your <b>BIOS</b> allows<br><b>non-secure</b> booting; then, it is the option you <b>should</b> select.
</p>
<p align="center">
Select a <b>drive</b> before <b>Continuing</b>.
</p>
